.TH "Simple_shell" "April 2022" "ms"
.hy
.SH SIMPLE SIMPLE_SHELL
.PP
.hsh [en]
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]\f[R] [OPTION]
.PD 0
.P
.PD

.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]\f[R] Simple shell - hsh it is a command and type of file that is responsible for executing commands that are read through the terminal.

.B COMMANDS
A command is an instruction that tells the operating system a task to perform. Some basic commands that are used allow the user to create, modify, delete or move files and folders. To execute commands, a terminal is required to execute them.

.RS
[\| ls \|]
The ls command can list file and directory information, including file type, owner, size, modification date and time, permissions, etc.

